WEBVTT

00:34.251 --> 00:35.992
I got it.

00:36.123 --> 00:39.561
I'm already awake.

00:55.185 --> 00:57.057
I'm coming.

01:04.673 --> 01:06.979
Where's my guy?

01:07.110 --> 01:08.807
There you are.

01:08.938 --> 01:11.680
You precious little angel.
Oh, yeah.

01:11.810 --> 01:14.987
Oh, thank you.

01:18.774 --> 01:20.776
I'll be right back.

02:01.077 --> 02:03.732
Mark! Mark! Mark!

02:06.735 --> 02:08.432
- What is it?
- Dylan's not in his crib!

02:08.563 --> 02:09.955
He's not in his crib!
He's not there!

02:10.086 --> 02:11.218
He's not there!
He's not there?

02:17.833 --> 02:19.530
911,
what's your emergency?

02:19.661 --> 02:21.141
I'm Susan,
I'm Susan Webster,

02:21.271 --> 02:22.968
and my son is...
I can't find my son.

02:23.099 --> 02:24.579
He's not in his crib!
I don't know

02:24.709 --> 02:26.407
if somebody took him
or what... what the--

02:26.537 --> 02:27.886
Ma'am,
are you alone?

02:29.497 --> 02:31.673
Whereabouts are you
in the house?

02:34.632 --> 02:36.156
Hello?

02:36.286 --> 02:37.940
Oh!

02:39.115 --> 02:41.161
Ma'am?

02:41.291 --> 02:43.424
Hello?

03:06.142 --> 03:08.275
Check her
blood pressure.

03:08.405 --> 03:10.929
Holy. Holy!

03:11.060 --> 03:12.366
- Keep pushing.
- It's okay. It's okay.

03:12.496 --> 03:14.368
- No, I can't!
- She's fine.

03:14.498 --> 03:16.979
- I mean. I can't...
I can't do it.

03:17.109 --> 03:19.851
- You can. You can.
You can. You're doing it.

03:19.982 --> 03:21.810
- Ready?
- You're doing it.

03:21.940 --> 03:25.379
- Okay. Okay.
- Three, two, one...

03:36.564 --> 03:40.263
It's a boy.

03:40.394 --> 03:42.091
It's a boy, babe. You did it.

03:43.571 --> 03:45.181
Oh, my God,
he's beautiful.

03:47.488 --> 03:49.098
We have a son.

04:04.113 --> 04:06.942
I'm so proud of you.

04:18.258 --> 04:20.085
Hello...

04:20.216 --> 04:22.914
Welcome to the world,
sweet boy.

04:23.045 --> 04:26.614
Hi. Yeah...

04:29.269 --> 04:32.446
I know, say what is Daddy
doing on his phone?

04:32.576 --> 04:34.926
Why? Why is he on his phone?

04:35.057 --> 04:37.886
Hmm?

04:39.714 --> 04:42.804
- Uh, sorry.
I'm... I'm sorry.

04:42.934 --> 04:45.110
I... I'm nervous. It's like,

04:45.241 --> 04:47.939
like coping mechanism
or something.

04:48.070 --> 04:50.855
Oh, hey mister.

04:50.986 --> 04:53.467
Hey, baby boy.
- Yeah. I know.

04:53.597 --> 04:56.470
- Can you believe it?
- I can't. This face.

04:56.600 --> 05:00.082
Yeah. I know. Shh.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.259
- I have a confession.

05:03.390 --> 05:06.828
I may have let your father know
that everything went great.

05:08.743 --> 05:11.398
- He's not here.
They're not here?

05:11.528 --> 05:13.051
- Yep.
- Mark. Ugh.

05:13.182 --> 05:15.663
- I'm sorry, babe. I just...

05:15.793 --> 05:17.012
I wanted to share this
with him, you know?

05:17.142 --> 05:18.666
He's like the father
I never had.

05:18.796 --> 05:20.494
That makes one of us.

05:20.624 --> 05:21.886
It's okay. It's okay.

05:22.017 --> 05:23.235
- Where is he?
- Hi!

05:23.366 --> 05:25.847
Where is that
grandson of mine?

05:25.977 --> 05:28.023
- Oh, I'm sorry.
- Hey, Neil. Ginny.

05:28.153 --> 05:30.417
- Well, what are we gonna,
what do we name him?

05:30.547 --> 05:33.202
- "We" named him Dylan.

05:33.333 --> 05:34.943
- Dylan?
- Oh!

05:35.073 --> 05:37.249
- Here we go. Here we go.
- Oh!

05:37.380 --> 05:39.034
- Oh, oh. It's okay, it's okay.
Just spit up a little.

05:39.164 --> 05:40.775
Hi. Dylan.

05:40.905 --> 05:44.213
Dylan sounds like
a loser kid in band camp.

05:44.344 --> 05:47.782
What about a more
manly name like Neil Jr.?

05:47.912 --> 05:50.698
'Cause he's not your son.

05:50.828 --> 05:52.090
- Yeah, well Neil Jr.
the third, then.

05:53.831 --> 05:55.180
- That's not
how names work, Dad.

05:55.311 --> 05:58.140
- No, he's Dylan, after Mom.

05:58.270 --> 06:01.665
- I don't want to jinx it,
but we just did IVF so Dylan

06:01.796 --> 06:04.886
might have a little uncle soon.

06:05.016 --> 06:07.715
- Wow, that's uh...
- There you go. There we go.

06:07.845 --> 06:10.935
- I um... I-I sent you
the press release.

06:11.066 --> 06:13.024
- Neil!
- Yeah, babe?

06:13.155 --> 06:14.678
- He's so handsome.
- Mm-hmm.

06:14.809 --> 06:16.506
I think he has my eyes.

06:16.637 --> 06:18.639
Well, that would be
surprising but, uh...

06:18.769 --> 06:21.076
- Yeah, so, I figured we could
discuss you know, my--

06:21.206 --> 06:24.122
- Mark... appreciate
the hustle. Take a break.

06:24.253 --> 06:27.038
Just uh... just enjoy
Neil Jr. there. Honey?

06:27.169 --> 06:28.562
- Oh! Ah!

06:28.692 --> 06:32.130
- No, still Dylan.
- Dad.

06:32.261 --> 06:34.089
- Oof.

06:38.223 --> 06:39.311
Mm-hmm.

06:47.929 --> 06:49.713
Yes, indeed,
in our bed.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.325
Surprise!

06:53.456 --> 06:55.023
- Aunt Peggy?!
- Wh--

06:55.153 --> 06:57.199
Oh, my God, he's so
precious.

06:57.329 --> 06:58.374
- What?!

06:58.505 --> 07:00.420
This is Dylan.
- Oh, my goodness.

07:00.550 --> 07:04.075
Well, I just had to go meet
this little man and...

07:05.599 --> 07:07.383
Ta-da!
- My blanket.

07:07.514 --> 07:09.167
Uh-huh.

07:09.298 --> 07:11.300
- Wait, did you,
did you do this?

07:11.431 --> 07:13.694
- Ah, please. He's so busy
on the construction

07:13.824 --> 07:15.130
of the Hollis building,
he doesn't even

07:15.260 --> 07:17.219
have time to construct
his own baby's crib.

07:17.349 --> 07:20.178
- Okay, zip it, Aunt Peg,
come on. You rat me out.

07:20.309 --> 07:21.745
What's goin' on?

07:21.876 --> 07:23.443
- Hey, listen,
never trust a journalist

07:23.573 --> 07:24.487
with her secrets, okay?

07:26.489 --> 07:29.753
Oh, my God.
- I know.

07:29.884 --> 07:32.539
Hey, little sis.

07:32.669 --> 07:36.194
Look what your daughter made.

07:36.325 --> 07:39.197
Dylan, that's your grandma.

07:39.328 --> 07:40.895
Mm-hmm.

07:41.199 --> 07:43.245
- Grandma, this is Dylan.

07:45.639 --> 07:49.556
I can't believe it.
I'm so happy for you.

07:54.474 --> 07:56.040
It's okay. Please,
please, please.

07:58.608 --> 08:01.219
Oh, please. Please, please.

08:01.350 --> 08:04.135
Okay, do you want a lullaby?
I can do a lullaby.

08:04.266 --> 08:05.789
I'm not a very good singer.
I could in college.

08:05.920 --> 08:07.617
I was in choir
for a little bit.

08:07.748 --> 08:09.924
- Hey, Suzie Q?
- Suz-- what? Hi.

08:10.054 --> 08:11.273
- You having trouble?

08:11.403 --> 08:13.405
- Yeah, he just, he won't
settle for a nap

08:13.536 --> 08:14.711
and I want to go to sleep.

08:14.842 --> 08:16.234
- Here, let me trying something.

08:16.365 --> 08:18.628
- Shh, Daddy's gonna try.

08:18.759 --> 08:21.152
- Oh, come on over.

08:21.283 --> 08:23.546
- Yeah, it's okay.
- Shh, shh, shh.

08:23.677 --> 08:26.157
Ah, there you go.

08:32.729 --> 08:35.166
- I was five when
my mom had Jacob.

08:35.297 --> 08:37.125
All he would do is cry.

08:38.213 --> 08:40.171
Aw.

08:42.652 --> 08:44.132
Okay.

08:50.704 --> 08:53.794
It was Jacob's comfort move.
- Mm-hmm.

08:53.924 --> 08:56.927
- Even when we got older,

08:57.188 --> 08:59.408
when my dad would rage,

08:59.539 --> 09:01.236
we'd hide in the tire well
of his car.

09:03.325 --> 09:05.588
The second I grabbed
Jacob's hand,

09:05.719 --> 09:07.285
just calmed right down.

09:10.462 --> 09:12.247
- He was lucky to have you.

09:15.555 --> 09:16.817
- Still can't believe
this is all real.

09:18.949 --> 09:20.777
I mean...

09:20.908 --> 09:23.519
I have a kid.

09:23.650 --> 09:25.521
This is my son. This thing.

09:25.652 --> 09:27.305
- Thing?!

09:27.436 --> 09:29.046
- You know what I mean.

09:30.308 --> 09:31.788
He is kind of a thing.

09:31.919 --> 09:33.529
Yeah.

09:36.227 --> 09:37.577
- And I'm his dad.

09:39.753 --> 09:41.450
How does this make any sense?

09:42.669 --> 09:46.542
- It's... crazy.

09:46.673 --> 09:48.370
For me, too.

09:54.202 --> 09:55.464
- Oh.

10:07.824 --> 10:10.522
- Oh! No.

10:10.653 --> 10:12.699
Oh, no, no, no.

10:19.575 --> 10:21.403
Ah!

10:24.754 --> 10:26.408
Yes, baby. Hi, hi,
hi, hi.

10:28.671 --> 10:31.587
Shh, shh, shh.

10:31.718 --> 10:35.852
I know, I know, I know.
I know, I know...

10:35.983 --> 10:38.333
Okay, okay. Okay.

10:38.463 --> 10:41.684
Okay. Okay,

10:41.815 --> 10:43.512
okay, okay.

10:45.819 --> 10:49.126
Oh, watch your head. Okay,
okay, okay.

10:51.259 --> 10:55.829
Shh. Shh. Oh, there we go.

10:55.959 --> 10:59.093
That's better. That's better.

11:03.706 --> 11:04.664
Holy sh--

11:04.794 --> 11:06.404
Mm...

11:06.535 --> 11:08.058
You're lucky

11:08.189 --> 11:11.279
it was just an ankle.
How did it happen?

11:11.409 --> 11:12.672
- I don't even know. Ah...

11:12.802 --> 11:15.718
one minute I had Dylan
down for a nap,

11:15.849 --> 11:19.243
and then I woke up to screaming,

11:19.374 --> 11:21.985
so I don't know, I must have
passed out or something.

11:22.116 --> 11:23.683
- Well, that happens
to the best of us.

11:25.032 --> 11:27.774
Hey. Hey, don't overthink it.

11:27.904 --> 11:32.604
Dylan's fine. Right?
Your ankle's not a big deal.

11:32.735 --> 11:33.823
- Hmm.
- Right?

11:33.954 --> 11:36.434
- Yeah, thanks.
- You're okay.

11:36.565 --> 11:40.743
- I know. I know it's just,
you know, at work I oversee

11:40.874 --> 11:43.180
an entire department of people.

11:43.311 --> 11:45.879
And I've never been as tired
as I am right now.

11:47.881 --> 11:50.492
- Well, newborns
are exhausting by design.

11:50.622 --> 11:52.537
It's mother nature's
little way of tricking us

11:52.668 --> 11:53.103
into doing it again.

11:53.408 --> 11:55.758
- Ha, ha, again. Sure.

11:57.804 --> 11:59.936
Hey, baby.

12:00.067 --> 12:01.721
- Whoa. What happened?

12:01.851 --> 12:03.984
- Oh, don't ask.

12:04.114 --> 12:05.942
- When did this happen? How?

12:06.073 --> 12:08.597
- It's not... it's not
a big deal. I'm fine.

12:08.728 --> 12:10.251
- Not a big deal. But--

12:10.381 --> 12:12.035
why haven't you called me?
Susan, you can't just

12:12.166 --> 12:14.559
have like a brok--

12:15.996 --> 12:17.606
And you're drinking.

12:18.999 --> 12:20.740
- I should go.

12:22.524 --> 12:24.395
Fine.

12:24.526 --> 12:26.746
- I'll call you.
- Yeah, please do.

12:26.876 --> 12:29.574
- Mark... always a pleasure.

12:33.883 --> 12:36.233
- Mark, what was that?!

12:36.364 --> 12:39.628
- What was--
- What? What is going on?

12:42.065 --> 12:45.547
Hey. Hey, hi. Hi. You have
a tell, you know.

12:45.677 --> 12:47.549
You look down and
to the left every time

12:47.679 --> 12:49.769
you're holding something back.
So, out with it. What?

12:52.336 --> 12:54.861
- Honestly, babe, I...

12:54.991 --> 12:56.863
I don't think you want
to hear what I have to say.

12:56.993 --> 12:58.647
- Try me.

13:00.388 --> 13:02.738
- What about getting some
help while you work?

13:05.001 --> 13:07.525
- Like a nanny?
- Yeah.

13:07.656 --> 13:12.443
- No! No, I don't want someone
else taking care of our son.

13:13.618 --> 13:15.620
- Ugh. remember ten seconds ago

13:15.751 --> 13:17.753
when I said you weren't gonna
want to hear what I had to say?

13:19.973 --> 13:25.326
- Okay. Mom brain is a real
thing. I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

13:25.456 --> 13:26.893
Oh, now who's drinking?

13:27.023 --> 13:30.070
- I am just showing
you solidarity.

13:30.200 --> 13:32.942
Uh-huh. I bet.

13:33.073 --> 13:35.292
It's okay,
I'm exhausted anyway.

13:41.821 --> 13:42.822
- Ooh.

13:48.001 --> 13:49.611
I'm positive I sent
it last night.

13:49.741 --> 13:50.960
Well,
nothing's in my inbox.

13:51.091 --> 13:53.658
- No, I stayed up extra late
doing it. Trust me...

13:53.789 --> 13:56.879
I can use all the sleep
I can get with a newborn.

13:57.010 --> 13:58.620
- I can imagine.
- Um, sorry, yeah, no,

13:58.750 --> 13:59.926
let me check.

14:00.056 --> 14:01.579
Take your time.

14:01.710 --> 14:03.755
- Okay...

14:03.886 --> 14:06.106
um...

14:06.236 --> 14:08.499
Just... I printed a copy.

14:08.630 --> 14:10.588
How's your son,
by the way?

14:10.719 --> 14:12.939
- He's good, thank you.

14:13.069 --> 14:14.984
I know I finished it I just...

14:15.115 --> 14:16.725
can't seem to fi--

14:16.856 --> 14:18.379
Look, I just need
it soon, okay?

14:18.509 --> 14:20.076
- Yes.
- All right.

14:20.207 --> 14:22.035
- As soon as I-, yes.
- I'm sure you'll find it.

14:22.165 --> 14:22.818
- Thank you.
- Bye, Susan.

14:22.949 --> 14:24.515
- Sorry.

14:28.868 --> 14:29.999
Are you sure you don't
wanna go back

14:30.130 --> 14:31.566
inside and sit down?

14:31.696 --> 14:34.569
- No, please, I could
use the fresh air.

14:36.049 --> 14:39.095
- Well... if Mark thinks
you need a nanny,

14:39.226 --> 14:42.707
then maybe he should consider
taking time off. That's fair.

14:42.838 --> 14:46.059
- My dad's breathing down his
neck with that legacy project,

14:46.189 --> 14:48.931
that Hollis building.
- Right.

14:49.062 --> 14:50.585
- I can't ask him to do that.

14:51.542 --> 14:52.674
- Sure.

14:55.633 --> 14:56.896
- Don't look at me like that.

15:00.421 --> 15:03.772
- Any chance this is
postpartum depression?

15:03.903 --> 15:08.733
- No! I don't...
I don't feel depressed. I...

15:08.864 --> 15:11.388
- Well, neither did my sister,
but she had it.

15:11.519 --> 15:14.304
And just like you,
she was tripping on things,

15:14.565 --> 15:15.871
sleeping all the time.

15:16.002 --> 15:16.959
Couldn't even remember
her own daughter's name.

15:36.239 --> 15:39.503
Susan, my God!
- I-- I didn't even see him.

15:39.634 --> 15:43.551
I...

15:43.681 --> 15:46.032
- Just breathe. Just breathe.

15:46.162 --> 15:48.512
Yeah.

15:54.214 --> 15:57.043
- I got it.
- Hmm...

15:57.173 --> 15:58.566
It's fine, I'm already awake.

16:03.832 --> 16:06.182
No! Mark! Mark!

16:06.313 --> 16:08.097
Dylan's not in his crib!

16:08.228 --> 16:09.620
He's not in crib!
He's not there!

16:09.751 --> 16:11.579
He's not there!
He's not there?

16:11.709 --> 16:14.060
- My name is Susan Webster.
I can't find my baby.

16:14.190 --> 16:15.583
He's not in crib and I just...

16:15.713 --> 16:17.063
I think somebody may have take--

16:17.193 --> 16:18.586
Ma'am,
are you alone?

16:21.023 --> 16:22.938
Whereabouts are
you in the house?

16:23.069 --> 16:26.594
Hello? Ma'am?

16:26.724 --> 16:28.335
Hello?

16:44.351 --> 16:46.092
- What?
- What's going on?

16:46.222 --> 16:47.919
- What? Where was he?

16:48.050 --> 16:49.312
- Shh, shh, shh.

16:49.443 --> 16:51.314
He was in his crib.

16:51.445 --> 16:54.839
- No. I checked
his crib. He wa...

16:54.970 --> 16:57.016
- Susan,

16:57.146 --> 16:58.930
I'm telling you,
he was in his crib.

16:59.061 --> 17:02.021
Is anyone there?
Can you hear me?

17:02.151 --> 17:03.761
- Hi, yeah.
- Is anyone hurt?

17:03.892 --> 17:05.937
- No, sorry. No, we're okay.

17:06.068 --> 17:07.896
A woman said there
was a missing baby.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.724
- My son's fine.

17:09.854 --> 17:10.899
Okay, call back
if you need us.

17:11.030 --> 17:12.683
- Thank you.

17:52.854 --> 17:54.029
- Hi, Susan.

17:59.426 --> 18:00.775
- Ahem.
- I appreciate you

18:00.905 --> 18:02.733
making the house call,
Dr. Riley.

18:02.864 --> 18:04.344
Oh, stop
with the "doctor", Mark.

18:04.474 --> 18:05.867
We've known each other
for how long?

18:08.826 --> 18:10.785
Wow.

18:10.915 --> 18:13.570
You're the spitting image
of your mother, by the way.

18:15.746 --> 18:16.486
- You knew my mom?

18:16.747 --> 18:19.968
Mm-hmm.

18:20.099 --> 18:23.058
We smoked our first cigarette
behind the school gymnasium.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.803
Delia was
a wonderful woman.

18:28.933 --> 18:31.327
- Yeah.

18:31.458 --> 18:33.416
Such a great mother.

18:33.547 --> 18:35.853
- Being a mother
is the greatest feeling,

18:35.984 --> 18:38.073
and the worst.

18:38.204 --> 18:40.771
You're constantly
second-guessing yourself.

18:40.902 --> 18:43.905
- Not her. She had
it all together.

18:44.035 --> 18:45.733
- Are you sure about that?

18:48.039 --> 18:52.479
All moms discover new
challenges, but the good ones,

18:52.609 --> 18:55.264
they shield
their children from it.

18:55.395 --> 18:57.310
- I don't feel like I'm doing
that for Dylan at all.

18:57.440 --> 19:01.836
- Before my youngest was born,

19:04.447 --> 19:07.842
I thought I knew what to expect.

19:07.972 --> 19:10.845
It wasn't long before
I was lying on the floor,

19:10.975 --> 19:14.892
picking up lint from
the carpet with my fingers.

19:15.023 --> 19:16.851
I had to make
major changes in my life

19:16.981 --> 19:19.810
just to break out
of the spiral.

19:20.811 --> 19:21.986
- How?

19:22.117 --> 19:24.772
- I started on meds.

19:24.902 --> 19:28.341
They saved my life,
and countless of my patients.

19:28.471 --> 19:32.432
And then I had to recognize that
bringing in someone part-time

19:32.562 --> 19:34.782
to help me didn't make me...

19:34.912 --> 19:37.959
less of a mom, but a better mom.

19:43.573 --> 19:45.140
- Tell me what you're
thinking, babe.

19:50.058 --> 19:51.842
- I'll do whatever it takes.

19:54.149 --> 19:55.977
Yeah, you're making
the right choice.

20:05.204 --> 20:07.031
There you go.

20:24.179 --> 20:25.615
- Amy.
- Hi. Hi, Mark?

20:25.920 --> 20:27.617
Yeah. Yeah, welcome.

20:27.748 --> 20:29.402
- Thank you so much.
- Yeah, come on in.

20:29.532 --> 20:31.926
You must be Susan?

20:32.056 --> 20:34.320
- Hi.
- Hi. Oh, he is so adorable.

20:34.450 --> 20:35.886
Mm-hmm.

20:36.017 --> 20:38.846
- May I?
- Uh... oh.

20:40.064 --> 20:42.980
Oh, sweet thing.
Thank you.

20:43.111 --> 20:44.808
Oh, look.

20:46.723 --> 20:48.377
[Mark: Oh, my God,
you're a natural.

20:55.950 --> 20:57.647
Are you awake for me?

20:57.778 --> 20:59.780
Are you gonna give me a nice
cuddle while you're awake

20:59.910 --> 21:00.998
from your nap, sweet boy?

21:26.937 --> 21:30.027
- Sugar frosted cereal
again? Breakfast sucks!

21:40.429 --> 21:42.213
Hey, hey, hey,
how ya doin'?

21:42.344 --> 21:47.306
Great. Here is your
cutest little prince.

21:47.436 --> 21:50.352
Oh, hey, big buy.
Oh, my God.

21:50.483 --> 21:52.136
Back to Daddy.

21:52.267 --> 21:53.486
Did you guys
have a nice day?

21:53.616 --> 21:56.010
We had such a good
day, didn't we, sir?

21:56.140 --> 21:58.012
Yes, do you want to tell him
all about it?

21:58.142 --> 22:01.102
Want to tell him what we did?

22:01.537 --> 22:04.018
The doctor will see you
now. Right this way.

22:12.679 --> 22:13.506
- Do you need some help?

22:13.636 --> 22:15.812
- I'm fine. Thanks.

22:23.298 --> 22:25.039
- So, what are those
pills you're taking?

22:27.171 --> 22:29.217
- Nortriptyline.
It's no big deal.

22:30.523 --> 22:31.306
- Is that safe, though?

22:32.612 --> 22:34.004
- Amy, do you have kids?

22:34.135 --> 22:37.747
- Uh, no. No, I'm um...

22:38.052 --> 22:39.749
I'm not lucky that way.

22:39.880 --> 22:42.186
That's why I do what I do.
These are my kids.

22:42.317 --> 22:45.059
- You don't have kids so you
don't understand, okay?

22:49.411 --> 22:52.240
I'm sorry.

22:52.371 --> 22:53.241
Sorry.
- It's okay.

22:55.809 --> 22:57.854
- The pills are for
my postpartum.

22:59.595 --> 23:01.989
They're prescribed
by a doctor and everything,

23:02.119 --> 23:04.339
so yes, they are perfectly safe.

23:05.514 --> 23:06.994
- Right.

23:12.216 --> 23:14.044
- S-Susan...

23:14.175 --> 23:15.698
Susan, you're bleeding.

23:16.003 --> 23:17.047
- What?

23:27.580 --> 23:29.103
Susan!

23:35.892 --> 23:36.850
Hey, sweet little guy.

23:39.069 --> 23:40.767
Hey, sweet little boy.

23:40.897 --> 23:45.293
Good job. Yeah, just like that.

24:00.961 --> 24:03.354
- Thank you for driving.

24:03.485 --> 24:05.313
- Yeah, no problem.
- Amy can you...

24:08.098 --> 24:09.796
please don't tell Mark
about this.

24:12.451 --> 24:13.321
- Yeah, right.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.160
- What, were you just
not gonna tell me?

24:26.290 --> 24:28.118
- Look, you had so
much going on!

24:28.249 --> 24:30.294
- Susan, h-how am I supposed
to help you if you're only

24:30.425 --> 24:31.470
telling me things
after they happen?!

24:31.600 --> 24:33.384
- You want to help me?

24:33.515 --> 24:35.604
Be here for me! Work less!

24:35.735 --> 24:37.737
Help out around the house more!

24:37.867 --> 24:41.305
I need support. I don't know
if I am just stressed.

24:41.436 --> 24:43.220
I don't know if it's
all the hormones?!

24:43.351 --> 24:44.570
I don't know if it's
these pills?!

24:44.700 --> 24:46.441
I don't know if I'm actually
losing my mind!

24:46.572 --> 24:49.226
But I have felt like I am doing
this by myself since day one.

24:49.357 --> 24:52.534
You haven't been here!
- Are you serious?! Oh, my God!

24:52.665 --> 24:54.797
That is so incredibly unfair.

24:54.928 --> 24:56.625
You know how hard it was
for me to watch

24:56.756 --> 24:58.018
my mother struggle alone.

24:58.148 --> 25:00.150
- No.
- I'm... I can't--

25:00.281 --> 25:01.717
No, this conversation's done.
- Mark--

25:01.848 --> 25:03.197
- I'm done with this
conversation.

25:16.515 --> 25:18.342
- Hey.

25:20.214 --> 25:22.477
I didn't ask you
for anything.

25:22.608 --> 25:25.001
Since you've been
here, not one thing.

25:25.132 --> 25:26.873
And the only time I do,

25:27.003 --> 25:28.657
you go straight to Mark
and you tell him?

25:28.788 --> 25:31.660
- I'm sorry, Susan. I just...
I was trying to help.

25:31.791 --> 25:34.271
- You were trying to help.

25:34.402 --> 25:39.015
If you want to help me,
don't meddle in my family.

25:39.450 --> 25:42.802
- Susan... I know that things
have been really hard for you.

25:42.932 --> 25:47.502
- Yes! Yes, it is hard!
It is very hard!

25:47.633 --> 25:49.330
And if I wanted it harder,

25:49.460 --> 25:52.376
I would have asked you
to meddle. And I didn't.

25:53.987 --> 25:56.293
You're done. Get out.
- Susan, please...

25:56.424 --> 25:57.512
- I said leave!

26:11.265 --> 26:13.093
- Susan...

26:21.405 --> 26:22.276
Susan?

26:25.714 --> 26:27.194
Where's Amy?

26:29.065 --> 26:30.327
- Gone.

26:35.724 --> 26:38.161
- Did you fire her?

26:38.292 --> 26:39.423
She couldn't
be trusted.

26:44.646 --> 26:47.693
- She was helping us.

26:47.823 --> 26:49.172
God, you're paranoid!

26:56.397 --> 26:57.964
How many of these
have you taken?

27:00.575 --> 27:03.273
- Enough to feel better.

27:08.583 --> 27:10.324
Baby...

27:12.674 --> 27:16.156
Baby... it's okay.

27:17.461 --> 27:20.160
We don't need...

27:20.290 --> 27:23.424
anyone in this house...

27:23.554 --> 27:25.339
that we can't trust.

27:26.949 --> 27:30.257
Right? We have everything...

27:32.476 --> 27:35.871
... we need...

27:36.132 --> 27:37.351
right...

27:38.613 --> 27:40.180
here.

27:42.748 --> 27:44.445
Right, baby?

27:50.494 --> 27:51.539
Right?

27:53.149 --> 27:55.108
- Okay.

27:55.238 --> 27:57.327
Okay. Okay!

28:00.504 --> 28:03.769
Look, baby...

28:03.899 --> 28:07.381
I'm gonna tell your father
that I'm working from home

28:07.511 --> 28:09.470
until we can get you back
on your feet.

28:12.473 --> 28:14.301
- What about
the Hollis building?

28:16.607 --> 28:18.435
- Doesn't matter.

28:18.566 --> 28:21.395
This is me choosing my family.

28:23.832 --> 28:26.052
I'm with you and Dylan.

28:28.619 --> 28:32.188
- Yeah.
- Okay. Come here, baby.

28:33.320 --> 28:35.235
We're gonna be okay.

28:37.193 --> 28:40.153
- You're gonna be...
- Mm...

29:03.959 --> 29:07.180
Here. Shh, shh, shh.

29:09.617 --> 29:12.446
Babe, do you want any
coffee? I'm making a pot.

29:14.709 --> 29:17.407
Speak now or forever
hold your peace.

29:17.538 --> 29:19.583
Can you get the baby, huh?

29:52.007 --> 29:55.532
Look at the water, baby...

29:55.663 --> 29:57.491
So beautiful...

29:59.580 --> 30:01.408
Just like you.

30:02.844 --> 30:06.326
Shh. Just like you.

30:23.647 --> 30:27.347
Baby, look...

30:27.477 --> 30:29.697
water's even prettier at night.

30:55.984 --> 30:58.204
Mr. Webster, could
you tell me what happened?

30:58.334 --> 31:02.338
I heard them outside
and so I came running out.

31:02.469 --> 31:05.341
I saw Susan at the end...

31:05.472 --> 31:07.604
of the... of the yard and...

31:09.824 --> 31:12.392
This is my boy's.
This is my boy's.

31:15.786 --> 31:19.007
There's nothing here.
This is... this is...

31:19.138 --> 31:20.704
go find him!
This isn't my son!

31:22.141 --> 31:23.577
He's not in here.

31:24.926 --> 31:27.276
Our son's not here.

31:27.407 --> 31:30.062
Where is he?
Where did you put him?

31:30.192 --> 31:33.239
Me? I... I didn't do it.

31:33.369 --> 31:35.328
- Baby.
- Where... where...

31:37.634 --> 31:40.768
No, I didn't... I don't...
I don't know. I don't know!

31:40.899 --> 31:43.902
I don't know!
Where is he?

31:44.032 --> 31:46.861
Where is he? Where is he?
Where is he?

31:46.992 --> 31:49.603
No! No, no, no.

31:53.433 --> 31:55.826
In local
news, Mrs. Susan Webster,

31:55.957 --> 31:58.786
daughter of construction
maven Neil Hollis,

31:58.917 --> 32:01.789
has now been charged
with manslaughter,

32:01.920 --> 32:05.924
even though the infant's
remains have yet to be found.

32:06.054 --> 32:10.885
Our own Dave Frang has spoken
with Mrs. Webster's physician,

32:11.016 --> 32:14.671
Nicole Riley, who prosecutors
claim will offer important

32:14.802 --> 32:18.284
key testimony in
Mrs. Webster's trial next week.

32:19.807 --> 32:22.070
- I was treating Susan
for postpartum depression,

32:22.201 --> 32:23.550
as I have with many other women.

32:23.680 --> 32:26.118
Nortriptyline is a
perfectly fine medicine

32:26.248 --> 32:29.730
for treating this. It's when
one abuses this medicine

32:29.860 --> 32:32.994
that we see all sorts
of tragic outcomes.

32:33.125 --> 32:34.865
- I've known Susan
since high school.

32:34.996 --> 32:37.738
It was clear that things
weren't coming naturally

32:37.868 --> 32:40.088
and I think she only made
it worse by pretending

32:40.219 --> 32:40.741
that everything was fine.

32:40.871 --> 32:42.917
- Bitch.

32:43.048 --> 32:45.876
- The one thing I have to say
about Susan Webster...

32:46.007 --> 32:47.269
she broke up her family.

32:47.400 --> 32:49.489
She never should have
been a mother!

32:51.578 --> 32:53.449
- Mr. Hollis, as the mother
of Mrs. Webster,

32:53.580 --> 32:54.842
and the grandfather
of the child,

32:54.973 --> 32:56.496
what do you have
to say about Susan's actions?

32:56.626 --> 32:58.019
- No comment.
- Just--

32:58.150 --> 32:59.499
- Get out of my--

33:03.503 --> 33:04.895
- Susan, you gotta stop
torturing yourself.

33:13.600 --> 33:15.906
- I just don't understand.

33:16.037 --> 33:18.779
My friends, my family?

33:21.086 --> 33:23.523
- They just don't know how
to make sense of it.

33:23.653 --> 33:25.568
- And I do?
- I didn't say that.

33:25.699 --> 33:27.701
- Well, it sounds like
you're on their side.

33:27.831 --> 33:29.616
- Baby, I'm...

33:29.746 --> 33:30.965
I'm not on anybody's side.

33:31.096 --> 33:32.706
- That's my point.

33:32.836 --> 33:36.014
You're supposed to be
on my side. I'm your wife.

33:36.144 --> 33:38.364
The mother of your...

33:40.844 --> 33:43.543
I don't know what happened.

33:44.979 --> 33:45.893
- Don't you?

33:46.981 --> 33:48.200
- Excuse me?

33:48.330 --> 33:50.158
- You weren't in your
right mind, right?

33:50.289 --> 33:52.813
- And where were you? Huh?

33:54.119 --> 33:55.729
What happened to
being here for us?

33:55.859 --> 33:57.209
- Hey, I did my best, okay?

33:57.339 --> 33:58.906
It's hard enough to raise
one kid, let alone two.

33:59.037 --> 34:00.777
- You're an ....

34:00.908 --> 34:03.084
- Yeah, well you're a failed
mother! You killed our son!

34:22.103 --> 34:24.845
I deserve to have
my side of the story told.

34:24.975 --> 34:27.195
It can be an exclusive.

34:27.326 --> 34:29.154
Please, Aunt Peggy, I-I...

34:29.284 --> 34:32.548
I'm not the monster
that everyone is saying I am.

34:32.679 --> 34:34.202
- I know that, kiddo!

34:34.333 --> 34:36.074
Honey, you're family.

34:36.204 --> 34:37.945
My producers are not
gonna touch this

34:38.076 --> 34:39.164
with a ten-foot pole.

34:39.294 --> 34:42.602
Especially with me anchoring
the story. Trust me!

34:42.732 --> 34:44.734
It's a conflict of interest.

34:45.561 --> 34:47.955
- I...

34:48.086 --> 34:49.913
I can't do this.

34:50.044 --> 34:52.351
- Hey... yes, you can.

34:54.222 --> 34:55.832
It's my work phone.

34:55.963 --> 34:59.706
Oh, huh, well speaking
of exclusives...

34:59.836 --> 35:02.491
"Mark Webster, husband
of Susan Webster,

35:02.622 --> 35:06.147
is calling on the people of this
community to grant his wife

35:06.278 --> 35:08.584
the space she needs
to grieve in peace."

35:08.715 --> 35:10.108
And he says, and I quote,

35:10.238 --> 35:12.153
"There is never a justification

35:12.284 --> 35:14.634
for terrorizing those
who are suffering."

35:15.852 --> 35:18.028
You see? Not everyone's
abandoning you.

35:22.337 --> 35:24.252
The Susan Webster
criminally negligent

35:24.383 --> 35:27.386
homicide trial is set
to begin next week.

35:27.516 --> 35:30.606
This case has shaken
the community to the core.

35:30.954 --> 35:33.131
Ladies and
gentlemen of the jury,

35:33.261 --> 35:34.871
the evidence will show--
The State would

35:35.002 --> 35:37.874
have you believe that this
was a premeditated act.

35:41.356 --> 35:44.838
Eight years. Can get out
in four though, right?

35:48.015 --> 35:50.017
The jury in this
controversial case

35:50.148 --> 35:51.366
has reached a verdict.

35:51.497 --> 35:53.977
Susan Webster
has been found guilty

35:54.108 --> 35:57.285
of criminally
negligent homicide.

35:59.809 --> 36:01.550
- We, we can do this, Susan.

36:01.681 --> 36:04.074
- Mark...

36:04.205 --> 36:06.860
it's a long drive.

36:06.990 --> 36:08.688
You should enjoy your weekend.

36:13.258 --> 36:15.260
- No...

36:15.390 --> 36:17.653
- I'm so sorry.

36:17.784 --> 36:19.699
- No, we can make
this work.

36:21.179 --> 36:23.833
We can.
- Goodbye, Mark. Goodbye.

36:23.964 --> 36:25.618
- Please, baby. Please don't
hang up the phone.

36:28.273 --> 36:30.318
Susan, please!

36:30.449 --> 36:33.060
Susan, don't walk away from me!

38:14.117 --> 38:16.250
- Uh, question,
where are the ba--

38:18.861 --> 38:20.820
...bathrooms?

38:25.651 --> 38:31.221
- I, for one, do not care what
you did... or didn't... do.

38:31.352 --> 38:33.485
So long as you're under
my watch, your focus

38:33.615 --> 38:37.271
is on moving forward.
Starting over.

38:37.402 --> 38:39.665
Don't think it'll work out.

38:39.795 --> 38:43.843
Don't tell yourself it'll be
okay. Didn't work out then,

38:43.973 --> 38:45.235
it's not gonna work out now.

38:45.366 --> 38:47.890
- Got it. Thanks.

38:48.021 --> 38:49.196
- Uh-huh.

38:51.416 --> 38:53.505
I always tell my parolees,

38:53.635 --> 38:55.115
if you're gonna remember
one thing:

38:55.245 --> 38:57.422
the past is not your friend.

38:57.552 --> 39:00.425
Okay.

39:00.555 --> 39:04.254
Go out into the world.
You are rehabilitated...

39:04.385 --> 39:06.474
Susan.

39:24.144 --> 39:26.886
- Uh... not gonna cover it.

39:29.018 --> 39:31.238
- What're you gonna do about it?

39:45.034 --> 39:46.384
- Hey.

39:46.514 --> 39:48.298
- What's up, new girl?

39:48.429 --> 39:50.083
- Slimeball stiffed me.

39:50.213 --> 39:52.346
Is there like,
protocol for that?

39:52.477 --> 39:54.740
Am I supposed to do something?
I don't wanna get him--

39:58.526 --> 40:00.267
- Hey, Jonnie boy...

40:00.398 --> 40:02.008
- What's up, Cassie?

40:02.138 --> 40:03.313
- You didn't finish your drink.

40:07.056 --> 40:08.928
Hey, get off me!
Get off me!

40:14.412 --> 40:17.284
- Thanks, Ramos.

40:21.723 --> 40:24.465
It's a good night.

40:24.596 --> 40:25.771
Keep the change.

40:28.208 --> 40:29.296
Cassie Mendoza.

40:31.298 --> 40:33.126
- Emma Cartwright.

40:33.256 --> 40:35.911
- Sure, gringa.
Drink after work?

40:46.313 --> 40:49.751
You know, I... I caught
my ex cheating on me.

40:49.882 --> 40:52.754
So then I started diving
into her life.

40:52.885 --> 40:56.976
I mean, I'm not proud of it
but... I'm definitely not sorry.

40:59.152 --> 41:03.809
Before I even knew it,
I was hooked.

41:03.939 --> 41:06.246
And everybody says
that hacking is a crime,

41:06.376 --> 41:12.078
but honestly, I call
it an artform. But even still...

41:12.208 --> 41:15.385
after a couple crooked wires
with the Mexican cartel,

41:15.516 --> 41:17.344
and a Russian bride later,

41:17.475 --> 41:19.259
it wasn't my ex
who went to prison.

41:21.174 --> 41:22.915
It was me.

41:26.092 --> 41:31.140
But look at me now, girl.
I'm reformed! I'm good.

41:33.099 --> 41:36.102
Just don't forget...
the past is not your friend.

41:36.232 --> 41:39.105
- Oh... you got
the same speech, huh?

41:39.235 --> 41:41.455
- Do you remember that
guy's mustache?

41:43.065 --> 41:45.198
Gringa, are you hungry?

41:45.328 --> 41:46.460
- I could eat.

41:46.591 --> 41:50.377
I...

41:50.508 --> 41:52.858
...can pay.

41:53.119 --> 41:55.208
Yeah!

41:55.338 --> 41:57.558
So much for fasting, right?

41:57.689 --> 41:59.386
Hey, yo, yo. Wait, wait.

41:59.517 --> 42:01.257
What?

42:01.388 --> 42:03.433
You are on the third
floor, aren't you?

42:03.564 --> 42:05.392
Yes, but you're never
gonna see my place--

42:26.369 --> 42:27.240
Cassie?

42:54.180 --> 42:56.443
Hey! Come back!

42:56.574 --> 42:58.271
What is this? Hey! Wait!

42:58.401 --> 43:02.405
No... stop! Stop,
please! Wait! Please!

43:05.757 --> 43:07.933
No! No, no, no, no!

43:15.593 --> 43:19.205
... Ha!

43:19.335 --> 43:19.422
Holy shit. Ha!

43:21.337 --> 43:25.211
Wow. You know...
I knew you looked familiar.

43:25.341 --> 43:26.952
I knew it.

43:27.082 --> 43:32.044
But... then again, all of
you Karens kinda blend, right?

43:32.174 --> 43:36.309
So... this doesn't mean
I gotta call you Emma, right?

43:36.439 --> 43:38.137
- I mean, you've been
calling me "gringa",

43:38.267 --> 43:39.529
whatever the hell that means.

43:39.660 --> 43:42.663
- I mean, it is better.

43:42.794 --> 43:46.058
Come on, don't be weird.
Sit down. Come on.

43:49.452 --> 43:52.107
So... I don't know you,
you don't know me,

43:52.238 --> 43:54.457
and I don't judge,

43:54.588 --> 43:57.591
but is there a world
that maybe your son isn't...

43:57.722 --> 44:00.376
you know...

44:02.422 --> 44:05.381
- They never found his body.

44:13.302 --> 44:15.609
- They're never gonna believe
me you were here.

44:27.882 --> 44:31.407
- Well, I still see Ginny
from time to time.

44:31.538 --> 44:33.714
Yeah? She ever get
that baby she wanted?

44:33.845 --> 44:37.631
- Uh, you mean, do you have
a step-sibling? Well, not yet.

44:37.762 --> 44:40.460
But I only hear bits
and pieces about your father.

44:40.590 --> 44:44.203
- Hmm. I'm sure you heard
how he disowned me.

44:44.333 --> 44:46.161
- Oh... Susan, that's cruel.

44:47.380 --> 44:48.816
- Whatever, that's fine.
I have moved on.

44:48.947 --> 44:51.601
Well... Mark hasn't.

44:51.732 --> 44:55.257
You know, he opened up a
women's health clinic downtown.

44:55.388 --> 44:56.824
Yeah, they have
the whole first floor

44:56.955 --> 44:58.478
of the Hollis Webster building.

44:58.608 --> 45:00.306
- Hollis Webster?

45:00.436 --> 45:02.134
- Mm-hmm. They're partners now.

45:02.264 --> 45:04.789
But... well, you've moved on.

45:04.919 --> 45:06.399
- Well, I've been trying to

45:06.529 --> 45:10.229
until someone slipped
this under my door.

45:16.626 --> 45:18.063
- What the hell is this?

45:18.890 --> 45:21.370
- There was a note. I...

45:21.501 --> 45:22.545
I just figured,
you're a reporter

45:22.676 --> 45:24.504
so maybe you could help me
verify it?

45:24.634 --> 45:26.549
- Honey, I'm a journalist,
not a magician.

45:26.680 --> 45:28.073
This can't be real.

45:28.203 --> 45:30.249
I mean, even if you want
it to be real.

45:30.379 --> 45:32.686
Even if I want it to be real.

45:32.817 --> 45:36.255
Susan, you've just got out
of prison. You're grieving.

45:36.385 --> 45:38.431
It's been four years!

45:38.561 --> 45:41.869
- I know. But the grief doesn't
just go away.

45:42.000 --> 45:44.045
It's part of who I am now.

45:44.176 --> 45:49.268
I need to know if this is real.
Please, Aunt Peggy, please.

45:51.574 --> 45:55.448
- Well... first you have
to consider

45:55.578 --> 45:58.407
who is willing to play
this cruel joke on you?

46:08.156 --> 46:09.375
I think we've got all
the information

46:09.505 --> 46:10.811
we need from you right now.

46:10.942 --> 46:13.292
I'll check in on
Friday and you'll be here?

46:13.422 --> 46:15.250
Yeah, I will be
here on Friday.

46:15.381 --> 46:17.296
Okay.
I'll see you then.

46:17.426 --> 46:18.645
- I'll see you then.
- Yeah.

46:23.737 --> 46:26.174
Oh, my God... Susan.

46:26.435 --> 46:30.309
- Hmm... technically
it's Emma Cartwright now.

46:31.527 --> 46:33.660
Hi, Ginny.

46:33.791 --> 46:35.488
- You have no business
being here.

46:37.751 --> 46:39.361
- I was just looking.

46:39.492 --> 46:43.713
But the Hollis Webster
building... it's a choice.

46:44.149 --> 46:48.022
- You have no idea how hard
it's been for the rest of us.

46:48.283 --> 46:49.284
- It's my name
on the building, too.

46:49.415 --> 46:51.156
- Really?

46:52.897 --> 46:55.464
I don't see Cartwright
written anywhere.

47:19.924 --> 47:22.578
Hey gringa,
que paso? It's Cassie.

47:22.709 --> 47:24.798
Listen, I'm not
gonna lie to you...

47:24.929 --> 47:28.193
our boss from the bar was too
spineless to tell you himself,

47:28.323 --> 47:31.544
so of course, he got me
to do it for him.

47:31.674 --> 47:35.722
Uh... I'm sorry, man.
He's letting you go.

47:35.853 --> 47:37.028
What?

47:37.376 --> 47:38.899
Someone tipped him off
about your past

47:39.030 --> 47:41.119
and now, well, everyone knows.

47:41.249 --> 47:45.166
He just doesn't want you
around his customers, right?

47:45.906 --> 47:48.778
But whatever, he's a jerk
anyways. Doesn't pay enough.

47:48.909 --> 47:50.824
Not enough hours.

47:50.955 --> 47:53.000
You can get over it, right?

47:53.131 --> 47:56.308
Hello?

48:02.923 --> 48:05.404
Mommy! Mommy!

49:01.851 --> 49:03.418
Gringa...

49:06.726 --> 49:08.467
You all right?

49:11.905 --> 49:15.822
You know if... if you wanna
blow off some steam,

49:15.953 --> 49:19.478
just meet me in the morning.
Vamonos.

49:38.671 --> 49:40.542
Hey... put a little weight
on your left foot.

49:40.673 --> 49:41.848
- I'm trying.
- A little weight,

49:41.979 --> 49:44.677
you slip, slip,
one, two. Come on.

49:44.807 --> 49:46.679
- Okay, okay.

49:48.855 --> 49:50.944
- No, get outta here. Get out.
I don't believe any of that.

49:51.075 --> 49:52.293
- I'm trying, man! I'm trying!

49:52.728 --> 49:56.863
- Light on your feet. Slip,
slip. One, two! Let me see it.

49:56.994 --> 49:59.474
Una... dos... tres!

49:59.605 --> 50:01.824
Mas! Mas! Mas!

50:03.783 --> 50:05.654
Woo!

50:07.352 --> 50:10.355
Ha, ha. Now you hit
like an ex-con.

50:12.922 --> 50:14.620
- What choice do I have?

50:14.750 --> 50:16.883
I don't have anyone else.

50:17.014 --> 50:19.712
Nobody's gonna walk in
and save the day for me.

50:19.842 --> 50:23.455
- Hey, babe... I look
like nobody to you?

50:25.109 --> 50:26.066
- What are you gonna do?

50:26.197 --> 50:28.155
- What I'm gonna do?
I'mma smack you!

50:28.286 --> 50:29.983
I've been helping
you all day.

50:30.114 --> 50:32.594
Now show me what you got! Duck!

50:32.725 --> 50:35.728
Eso. But you know what?

50:35.858 --> 50:37.730
You're starting
to smell real bad.

50:37.860 --> 50:39.906
So, if I'm gonna help
you, you gotta go shower.

50:40.037 --> 50:42.648
Like, quick! 'Cause you're
gonna stink up my car.

50:48.306 --> 50:50.482
So, which one's Ginny?

50:50.612 --> 50:51.918
The bleached blonde.

50:52.049 --> 50:54.921
- Aye, aye, aye!
She married your dad?

50:56.966 --> 50:59.578
- She's been trying to have
a baby with him for years now.

50:59.708 --> 51:01.623
- Oh, a new little brother, huh?

51:01.754 --> 51:03.973
Oh, God, I hope not.

51:04.104 --> 51:05.845
But if I had to bet,

51:05.975 --> 51:07.064
she's the one that's
been following me

51:07.194 --> 51:09.675
in that silver station wagon.

51:09.805 --> 51:11.503
Hate to break it
to you, that don't look like

51:11.633 --> 51:13.026
no silver station wagon to me.

51:13.157 --> 51:14.897
- No, it does not.

51:16.943 --> 51:19.772
- Okay. So, who else has
you on their shit list?

51:39.705 --> 51:41.141
- Hey...

51:41.272 --> 51:45.624
can you look up Nicole Riley?
Dr. Nicole Riley?

51:46.015 --> 51:48.801
She was the one who prescribed
me my postpartum meds.

51:48.931 --> 51:50.629
Okay.

51:52.544 --> 51:53.936
Whew...

51:54.067 --> 51:55.764
- Oh, my God.

51:57.244 --> 51:59.812
Literally posted
two days ago.

51:59.942 --> 52:03.076
- Huh. Her car...

52:03.207 --> 52:05.644
- The infamous silver wagon.

52:12.477 --> 52:16.524
Ooh, nice
neighborhood. I don't know, man.

52:16.655 --> 52:17.656
You sure about this?

52:17.786 --> 52:19.484
Oh, let's just do it.

52:24.402 --> 52:26.491
Uh, gringa...

52:27.927 --> 52:29.711
- Hi, Mark.

52:29.842 --> 52:31.974
- Susan...

52:32.105 --> 52:35.804
Wow. Uh...

52:35.935 --> 52:38.633
I... I'm at a loss.
I don't know what to say.

52:40.157 --> 52:41.680
- Uh... you look good.

52:46.250 --> 52:48.121
- What's up with your friend?

52:48.252 --> 52:50.515
- Oh, uh, Cassie.

52:52.908 --> 52:56.173
Um...

52:56.303 --> 52:58.740
did you read about Dr. Riley?

52:58.871 --> 53:02.309
- Yeah, that's uh...
just awful. It's tragic.

53:02.440 --> 53:05.356
- Yeah. The weird thing is,

53:05.486 --> 53:08.185
I think that she
was following me.

53:08.576 --> 53:10.839
Why... why would
she be following you?

53:10.970 --> 53:14.016
- I don't know, but she
slid this under my door.

53:14.147 --> 53:16.715
And...

53:16.845 --> 53:19.544
I thought you should...
see them.

53:25.854 --> 53:27.029
I mean,
if that's real...

53:27.160 --> 53:27.943
- You're sick.

53:28.074 --> 53:29.858
- What?!

53:29.989 --> 53:31.730
- Why would you do
this to me, Susan?

53:31.860 --> 53:34.863
- If that's real,
he could still be al--

53:34.994 --> 53:36.778
- I don't want any part
of this, Susan.

53:36.909 --> 53:38.519
- Mark!
- Stay outta my life.

53:39.781 --> 53:41.130
Get yourself
some help, Susan.

53:50.183 --> 53:52.751
They're all the same.

53:54.318 --> 53:56.624
Not what you expected, huh?

53:57.146 --> 53:58.757
; You know what,
let's get outta here.

54:32.269 --> 54:33.922
Susan?

54:36.055 --> 54:37.796
Oh, my God!

54:41.234 --> 54:44.193
Uh...

54:44.324 --> 54:46.021
it's been a long time.

54:46.152 --> 54:47.719
- Four years.

54:49.329 --> 54:51.026
- How've you been?

54:51.157 --> 54:52.767
You look good.

54:56.336 --> 55:00.993
Sweetie, Mommy's just talking
to an old friend, okay?

55:01.123 --> 55:03.822
Why don't you go and choose
a chocolate bar

55:03.952 --> 55:06.085
and I'll be right over? Okay?

55:09.262 --> 55:10.829
"Old friend"?

55:14.267 --> 55:17.009
- Susan...

55:17.139 --> 55:18.010
I'm so sorry.

55:20.099 --> 55:22.971
No, I-I mean it.

55:23.102 --> 55:25.539
I'll never forgive myself
for what I said publicly when...

55:25.844 --> 55:27.802
you were my best friend.

55:29.891 --> 55:32.067
- What do you want, Alice?

55:32.198 --> 55:33.982
- The truth was, I was really
messed up back then.

55:35.549 --> 55:38.726
It's not an excuse but...

55:38.857 --> 55:41.076
my sister never had
postpartum depression.

55:41.207 --> 55:45.211
It was me. And I didn't tell you
because I don't know...

55:45.342 --> 55:47.996
shame, I guess.

55:54.307 --> 55:57.397
- It's okay. I'm sorry.

55:57.528 --> 56:00.269
- I just wasn't thinking
straight back then.

56:00.400 --> 56:03.055
And just like you,
I was on Nortriptyline.

56:03.185 --> 56:05.797
But sometimes those
little red pills just...

56:05.927 --> 56:06.928
wouldn't work, you know?

56:08.365 --> 56:10.018
- Red pills?

56:12.499 --> 56:14.196
- Uh yeah, I... I have to go.

56:15.415 --> 56:16.851
I'll call you. Okay?

56:18.287 --> 56:19.724
Sweetie...

56:30.691 --> 56:32.911
You're all set
up for the next three weeks

56:33.041 --> 56:34.303
but if you notice any
side effects at all,

56:34.434 --> 56:36.044
just give us a call back--

56:36.175 --> 56:37.872
- Nortriptyline.
- Wh-what?

56:38.003 --> 56:40.048
- Nortriptyline,
is it red or is it blue?

56:40.179 --> 56:41.963
- Uh... it... ma'am.
I don't--

56:42.094 --> 56:44.313
- The pills... are they
red or are they blue?!

56:44.444 --> 56:46.098
- They're red. They're red.

56:46.228 --> 56:48.056
- Are you sure?
- I have a sample.

56:48.187 --> 56:49.101
- Okay.

56:49.231 --> 56:51.538
It's uh...

56:51.669 --> 56:54.106
- Come on!
- Oh, uh...

56:57.544 --> 56:59.111
- Have they ever been
prescribed as a blue pill?

56:59.241 --> 57:01.113
No.

57:01.243 --> 57:02.331
I appreciate you

57:02.462 --> 57:03.681
making the house call,
Dr. Riley.

57:03.811 --> 57:05.334
Stop with
the "doctor",

57:05.465 --> 57:07.293
Mark. We've known
each other for how long?

57:07.424 --> 57:10.209
You're the spitting image
of your mother, by the way.

57:17.390 --> 57:18.260
- It's always been red.

57:21.350 --> 57:24.136
- You... you drugged me?

57:26.138 --> 57:29.881
You drugged me?!
You drugged me! You psycho!

57:30.011 --> 57:31.926
- Get her outta here.
- Don't you... you're insane!

57:32.057 --> 57:33.754
You had her killed?!

57:33.885 --> 57:36.017
Every-, everything's
gonna be fine. It, it's fine.

57:38.455 --> 57:40.935
- Everything's fine,
like she says. Kendra...

57:41.066 --> 57:42.807
take an early lunch.

57:49.074 --> 57:51.293
Cassie?

57:51.424 --> 57:53.252
Cassie, I just saw Mark.

57:53.382 --> 57:57.952
He was switching my pills with
my doctor, the whole time!

58:04.568 --> 58:06.178
Someone trashed your place?

58:06.308 --> 58:08.267
- No, I just decided
to redecorate.

58:14.273 --> 58:16.275
I knew your boy
was eyeing me up.

58:16.405 --> 58:18.756
- This is my fault?

58:19.017 --> 58:20.409
I'm so sorry.

58:20.540 --> 58:23.369
- Well, shit... you're
on a roll, detective.

58:23.500 --> 58:25.023
- This was Mark.

58:25.153 --> 58:26.938
- You know you sound
crazy, right?

58:28.766 --> 58:31.682
Look, just...

58:31.812 --> 58:34.206
hear me out. Listen,
look at me. Please, please.

58:34.336 --> 58:36.730
Dr. Riley was the one who
slipped me the photo of Dylan.

58:36.861 --> 58:40.038
She was the one
swapping out my meds.

58:40.168 --> 58:41.605
Mark brought
her into our house.

58:41.735 --> 58:43.563
Said that they knew each other
for years and...

58:43.694 --> 58:46.131
and now she's dead?

58:46.566 --> 58:50.222
I know it sounds crazy, but
that doesn't mean it's not true.

58:50.352 --> 58:52.224
Please...

58:54.618 --> 58:56.881
Cassie...

58:58.143 --> 59:00.058
Mark can't get away
with this.

59:05.193 --> 59:07.892
Help me clean up this mess...

59:08.022 --> 59:10.068
and I'm gonna help you
clean yours.

59:12.549 --> 59:14.072
Okay.

59:18.206 --> 59:21.470
I don't know Spanish.

59:31.872 --> 59:34.919
Okay... welcome back.

59:35.876 --> 59:38.183
I want the gate closed... now.

59:38.313 --> 59:41.186
Okay, amigos,
we're closed!

59:41.316 --> 59:43.449
I want everybody out, now!

59:43.580 --> 59:46.191
You too, Grandpa.
Bakery's closed!

59:46.321 --> 59:47.932
Hey, girl.

59:50.630 --> 59:52.414
Susan, come here.

01:00:03.338 --> 01:00:07.038
Keep an eye on the door, yeah?
Gracias.

01:00:07.168 --> 01:00:13.131
Okay, so your boy trashed my
laptop back at the apartment.

01:00:14.393 --> 01:00:15.481
- Not "my boy".

01:00:15.612 --> 01:00:18.397
- Well, luckily,
any self-respected hacker,

01:00:18.527 --> 01:00:22.183
muchas gracias, always has
one or two weapons of choice

01:00:22.314 --> 01:00:23.968
laying around.

01:00:25.883 --> 01:00:27.580
Okay, gringa... you ready?

01:00:27.711 --> 01:00:29.321
- Yeah.
- Let's dig.

01:00:33.499 --> 01:00:35.501
That means I need his
last name, birth place,

01:00:35.632 --> 01:00:37.155
age, parents...

01:00:37.285 --> 01:00:39.505
- Webster. Mark Andrew Webster.

01:00:39.636 --> 01:00:41.463
Raised in Tampa.
Went to Syracuse.

01:00:41.594 --> 01:00:43.683
Born October 14th, 1985.

01:00:43.814 --> 01:00:45.337
- Any fetishes?

01:00:46.425 --> 01:00:47.513
- What?

01:00:47.644 --> 01:00:48.993
- Nah, I'm just kidding.

01:00:49.123 --> 01:00:50.429
You shoulda seen your face
though. What?!

01:00:51.952 --> 01:00:53.606
- Wait, what are you doing?

01:00:53.737 --> 01:00:55.477
- Don't ask.

01:00:55.608 --> 01:00:57.697
Is it legal?

01:00:57.828 --> 01:01:00.134
- What did I just say?

01:01:00.265 --> 01:01:01.570
Back up. Back up.

01:01:01.701 --> 01:01:03.921
You make me nervous.
Back up. One more step.

01:01:04.051 --> 01:01:05.531
I can smell you.
- Sorry. Okay, okay.

01:01:12.886 --> 01:01:15.062
- Did he ever change his name?

01:01:15.454 --> 01:01:17.195
- Mark? No.

01:01:19.414 --> 01:01:21.329
- Well, I don't know.
Don't shoot the messenger.

01:01:21.460 --> 01:01:23.114
Take a look.

01:01:23.680 --> 01:01:28.293
Med student in Utah,
engaged to a Mark Reynolds.

01:01:28.423 --> 01:01:30.382
Filed for a restraining order.

01:01:30.512 --> 01:01:32.384
- Oh, pfft...

01:01:32.514 --> 01:01:34.212
oh, my God.

01:01:36.867 --> 01:01:38.172
Wait, who's that one?

01:01:38.303 --> 01:01:40.218
- Don't touch my screen.
- Sorry.

01:01:42.263 --> 01:01:44.396
- Jackie Mitchell?

01:01:44.526 --> 01:01:47.442
Picture was taken in Idaho.

01:01:47.573 --> 01:01:48.400
Let me zoom in.

01:01:49.706 --> 01:01:51.490
I mean...

01:01:51.620 --> 01:01:54.406
Ugh! They look like they were
practically still kids.

01:01:54.536 --> 01:01:56.060
Oh, my God!

01:01:56.190 --> 01:01:57.931
- Not a big deal.
It's just an ex-wife.

01:01:58.062 --> 01:02:00.412
- No, that...
that was our nanny!

01:02:00.542 --> 01:02:02.719
- Okay.

01:02:02.849 --> 01:02:05.809
So, you're telling me that
he hired his child bride

01:02:05.939 --> 01:02:07.636
as your nanny?
- Um...

01:02:07.767 --> 01:02:10.030
- Now that's a fetish.
- Can you get me an address?

01:02:10.161 --> 01:02:12.467
Already texted you.

01:02:12.598 --> 01:02:13.338
- Thank you, okay.

01:02:16.254 --> 01:02:16.994
Can I borrow your car?

01:02:19.605 --> 01:02:22.564
- You're lucky I like you.
You break it, you buy it!

01:02:22.695 --> 01:02:23.652
- Thank you!

01:02:43.760 --> 01:02:45.631
All right, you were
able to make a decision?

01:02:45.762 --> 01:02:47.285
Good choice.

01:02:52.812 --> 01:02:55.946
Great choice. Um, that's $40
for everything, please.

01:02:56.076 --> 01:02:58.775
Perfect. Thank you, Jenny.
Great.

01:02:58.905 --> 01:03:05.303
All right. Well, I am very
much looking forward to see you.

01:03:05.433 --> 01:03:07.871
Oh, and uh, I was meaning
to ask you,

01:03:08.001 --> 01:03:10.047
it's been a long time since
I've seen Nonna.

01:03:10.177 --> 01:03:13.180
Will you say hello to her for
me? Okay, thank you so much.

01:03:25.889 --> 01:03:27.716
Excuse me, ma'am?

01:03:27.847 --> 01:03:29.501
Can I... can I help you
with something?

01:03:30.981 --> 01:03:33.722
Tell me what you did
to my son...

01:03:33.853 --> 01:03:35.681
Jackie.

01:03:35.812 --> 01:03:37.422
Susan!

01:03:39.554 --> 01:03:41.339
God, you frickin' psycho!

01:03:41.469 --> 01:03:44.733
Tell me what happened!

01:03:46.910 --> 01:03:48.955
- Nothing!
You're certifiably insane!

01:03:49.086 --> 01:03:52.393
- I'm insane? What's insane

01:03:52.524 --> 01:03:56.702
is my husband's ex-wife
posing as our nanny!

01:03:56.833 --> 01:03:58.965
- No, I was just trying to
help you get back on your feet.

01:03:59.096 --> 01:04:02.316
It wasn't like that.
- Tell me the damn truth!

01:04:02.447 --> 01:04:04.579
- It is the truth! Please!

01:04:04.710 --> 01:04:06.668
Mark... Mark... all he ever
wanted was a family

01:04:06.799 --> 01:04:08.018
and it killed him
to see you struggle.

01:04:08.148 --> 01:04:11.412
- I was struggling because
Mark had me drugged!

01:04:11.543 --> 01:04:13.632
What did you do?!
- What do you mean

01:04:13.762 --> 01:04:15.721
he had you drugged?
What do you mean?

01:04:15.852 --> 01:04:17.418
If that's the truth then he
was taking advantage of me too.

01:04:17.549 --> 01:04:18.680
I didn't know! Please!

01:04:27.298 --> 01:04:27.864
- Talk.

01:04:29.909 --> 01:04:32.651
- It was... it was his idea not
to tell you the truth.

01:04:34.522 --> 01:04:36.568
He said that it
would set you off.

01:04:38.091 --> 01:04:39.571
I mean, can you blame him?

01:04:43.140 --> 01:04:44.576
Okay, you want
the truth, Susan?

01:04:46.708 --> 01:04:48.754
It was a long time ago,
all right?

01:04:51.713 --> 01:04:54.064
But I loved him.

01:04:54.194 --> 01:04:56.457
I never stopped loving him.

01:04:56.588 --> 01:04:58.242
Ever since we were kids.

01:04:59.504 --> 01:05:01.723
And then he needed me.

01:05:01.854 --> 01:05:02.899
And I mean, hell,
you needed me.

01:05:03.029 --> 01:05:05.162
- Not good enough.

01:05:05.292 --> 01:05:07.599
- Do you remember when you
asked me if I had kids?

01:05:09.253 --> 01:05:12.778
And I said I wasn't lucky
that way?

01:05:12.909 --> 01:05:15.824
We were pregnant once.

01:05:15.955 --> 01:05:18.827
But life had other plans.

01:05:18.958 --> 01:05:20.612
An abortion is the last thing
that I wanted

01:05:20.742 --> 01:05:22.440
but I didn't have a choice.

01:05:24.616 --> 01:05:28.402
And then in you,
and in Mark, and then...

01:05:28.533 --> 01:05:32.015
your beautiful...

01:05:32.145 --> 01:05:36.628
baby boy, I saw a second chance
to be a mom, I guess.

01:05:36.758 --> 01:05:38.630
I know it's stupid.
I know, okay?

01:05:40.762 --> 01:05:42.547
I truly wanted to help, Susan!

01:05:44.549 --> 01:05:46.594
I'm sorry that I failed you.

01:05:47.769 --> 01:05:51.469
I... I don't know what
happened to Dylan.

01:05:51.599 --> 01:05:52.644
I swear.

01:05:53.950 --> 01:05:54.820
I loved him too.

01:05:57.910 --> 01:06:01.044
I saw more than anyone how
much you loved him.

01:06:01.174 --> 01:06:03.655
You deserve to know the truth
after all these years.

01:06:08.921 --> 01:06:10.575
Your lip is bleeding.

01:06:11.837 --> 01:06:12.664
- So is your face.

01:06:18.322 --> 01:06:20.498
- I'll get you a cloth
from the back.

01:06:27.635 --> 01:06:30.725
- Chicos, we open in ten
minutes. Hurry up.

01:06:30.856 --> 01:06:33.511
Andele,
let's go.

01:06:37.819 --> 01:06:41.519
What? You found
something? Let me see.

01:06:45.958 --> 01:06:47.438
Dang!

01:06:51.833 --> 01:06:55.228
Dios mio...

01:06:59.145 --> 01:07:01.365
Now that is next-level crazy.

01:07:04.281 --> 01:07:06.239
- Take care, Susan.

01:07:06.500 --> 01:07:08.720
No offense, but uh...

01:07:08.850 --> 01:07:09.895
I hope I never see you again.

01:07:10.026 --> 01:07:12.550
- Hmm. Ditto.

01:07:33.005 --> 01:07:34.615
Where is he?!

01:07:36.661 --> 01:07:37.575
That's his blanket.
Where is he?

01:07:37.705 --> 01:07:39.794
You lied?! Where is he?

01:07:39.925 --> 01:07:42.406
Just tell me where he is,
please. Please, please,

01:07:42.536 --> 01:07:44.582
just tell me where he is.

01:07:44.712 --> 01:07:46.888
Please, please, please, please.

01:07:47.019 --> 01:07:48.586
Please, just tell me
where he is.

01:07:48.716 --> 01:07:51.719
No, no, no. No, no.
You called the cops?!

01:08:03.905 --> 01:08:05.733
- Emma Cartwright...

01:08:05.864 --> 01:08:07.779
that's original.

01:08:07.909 --> 01:08:09.433
I warned you what
would happen if you went

01:08:09.563 --> 01:08:13.089
digging around in your past.
Lo and behold, here we are.

01:08:13.219 --> 01:08:15.700
- Please, you have to listen
to me. My son is alive.

01:08:15.830 --> 01:08:19.007
- No, you didn't listen to me...
when you had a chance.

01:08:19.138 --> 01:08:21.923
Well, buckle up, Cartwright.
You're going back to prison!

01:08:32.891 --> 01:08:34.588
- Hollis, you got a visitor.

01:08:45.077 --> 01:08:46.818
- Hey, Suzie Q.

01:08:53.912 --> 01:08:55.479
You poor thing.

01:08:58.177 --> 01:09:00.048
Still pushing away
the people you love, huh?

01:09:00.179 --> 01:09:02.921
- I know what you did.

01:09:04.183 --> 01:09:06.011
- Do you?

01:09:06.142 --> 01:09:08.840
- You brought your ex-wife
into our home.

01:09:08.970 --> 01:09:10.624
- My ex-wife?

01:09:10.755 --> 01:09:12.496
- I know about
the baby you lost.

01:09:14.802 --> 01:09:19.111
Why would you give her Dylan?
He was ours.

01:09:19.242 --> 01:09:20.852
He was mine!

01:09:23.028 --> 01:09:24.682
- I have no idea what
you're talking about.

01:09:24.812 --> 01:09:27.075
- I saw his blanket!

01:09:27.206 --> 01:09:30.949
The pictures, the documents,
they're real. He is alive!

01:09:31.079 --> 01:09:34.692
- Come on, Susan. Your grasp
on reality is tenuous at best.

01:09:34.822 --> 01:09:37.042
- No, you had
Dr. Riley drug me.

01:09:37.173 --> 01:09:40.306
Only you didn't count
her growing a conscience

01:09:40.437 --> 01:09:42.047
four years later... did you?

01:09:50.273 --> 01:09:51.709
Why are you here?

01:09:53.928 --> 01:09:55.495
- I'm just doing my duty as
a grieving father,

01:09:55.626 --> 01:09:58.237
trying to get through to his
mentally unstable ex-wife.

01:09:58.368 --> 01:10:00.761
Some people would consider
that sympathetic.

01:10:00.892 --> 01:10:02.372
- You're sociopathic.

01:10:02.502 --> 01:10:05.113
- Whatever helps you
sleep at night, Susan.

01:10:05.244 --> 01:10:07.028
And I'm sure it's hard
to sleep at night.

01:10:08.421 --> 01:10:10.031
All those horrible memories.

01:10:11.032 --> 01:10:13.034
Say...

01:10:14.949 --> 01:10:16.690
have you tried medication?

01:10:20.520 --> 01:10:24.132
- I know who you are.
People know who you are...

01:10:24.263 --> 01:10:25.743
Mark Mitchell.

01:10:29.268 --> 01:10:31.139
- Well...

01:10:31.270 --> 01:10:32.837
I really must be going.

01:10:35.361 --> 01:10:36.884
I gotta see a girl
about a laptop.

01:10:38.277 --> 01:10:40.801
Guards!
- No.

01:10:40.932 --> 01:10:41.672
You leave Cassie out of this.

01:10:41.802 --> 01:10:42.803
You leave Cassie
out of this!

01:10:42.934 --> 01:10:44.457
Come on!
Come on, let's go!

01:10:44.588 --> 01:10:45.980
- She had nothing
to do with this. No!

01:10:46.111 --> 01:10:47.808
- Get her out.
- You leave her alone!

01:10:47.939 --> 01:10:49.767
He's gonna hurt my friend! No!

01:10:56.904 --> 01:11:00.691
- Hollis, let's go.
You're getting transported.

01:11:00.821 --> 01:11:02.693
Where?

01:11:02.823 --> 01:11:04.956
- Back to a
minimum-security facility.

01:11:16.663 --> 01:11:19.971
So, you looking forward to
going back to your old cell?

01:11:26.064 --> 01:11:28.109
How do you sleep
at night?

01:11:28.240 --> 01:11:30.808
- What the...

01:11:34.159 --> 01:11:36.204
Get outta the road!

01:11:36.335 --> 01:11:39.730
Come on! Move it, let's go!

01:11:42.254 --> 01:11:44.778
That's it!

01:11:45.257 --> 01:11:47.955
I told you guys, get off
the damn road!

01:11:48.086 --> 01:11:50.349
Now! Move it! Let's go!

01:11:50.480 --> 01:11:53.004
I'll drag you down the street.

01:11:53.134 --> 01:11:54.484
Think I'm kidding?
I'll have you arrested.

01:11:56.268 --> 01:11:58.226
No! No! No!

01:11:58.357 --> 01:12:00.011
No!

01:12:03.188 --> 01:12:04.145
- Oh my... oh, my God.

01:12:06.322 --> 01:12:07.235
Cassie!

01:12:11.414 --> 01:12:13.764
Cassie?

01:12:19.335 --> 01:12:22.642
No! No! No!

01:12:22.773 --> 01:12:24.035
Cassie!

01:12:24.165 --> 01:12:26.864
No, no, no. Stay.

01:12:26.994 --> 01:12:29.040
Stay with me. Hey, hey.

01:12:29.170 --> 01:12:30.389
- I'm s-sorry.

01:12:30.520 --> 01:12:32.260
- You put up a hell of a fight.

01:12:32.391 --> 01:12:34.088
- Ma--
- I'm so sorry.

01:12:34.219 --> 01:12:35.873
Mark...

01:12:36.003 --> 01:12:38.179
- I'm so sorry. Shh,
stay with me. Stay with me.

01:12:40.356 --> 01:12:42.401
T-t-t-take this.

01:12:42.532 --> 01:12:44.664
Please. Please! No!!

01:12:49.103 --> 01:12:51.279
No!

01:12:55.371 --> 01:12:57.155
What?

01:13:50.426 --> 01:13:53.472
You never had
a brother, did you?

01:13:53.603 --> 01:13:57.128
Jackie's your sister!
You sick bastard!

01:14:00.174 --> 01:14:02.133
- Susan, you really shouldn't
have come here.

01:14:09.140 --> 01:14:11.055
- You lied to me
about everything!

01:14:11.185 --> 01:14:13.971
- Ah!
- Start talking.

01:14:14.101 --> 01:14:15.973
Our father
forced us!

01:14:16.103 --> 01:14:19.367
If we refused, Susan,
he beat us!

01:14:21.761 --> 01:14:24.068
I almost didn't
make it out alive.

01:14:24.198 --> 01:14:26.505
And... and Jackie
was never the same.

01:14:26.636 --> 01:14:29.595
The complications
from her abortion meant

01:14:29.726 --> 01:14:32.032
she can never have
another baby.

01:14:32.163 --> 01:14:34.470
And right before Dylan
was born, she...

01:14:34.600 --> 01:14:37.168
she threatened to expose me
if I didn't give him to her!

01:14:37.298 --> 01:14:41.172
I was... I was gonna lose
everything! I mean...

01:14:41.302 --> 01:14:43.261
- I never had postpartum, did I?

01:14:43.391 --> 01:14:45.437
- No... no, you didn't.

01:14:47.265 --> 01:14:50.050
- The tea.
You put something in my tea!

01:14:50.181 --> 01:14:52.357
I was so tired.

01:14:52.488 --> 01:14:55.621
The night Dylan went
missing, that was you!

01:14:55.752 --> 01:14:58.015
- That was us! That was us!

01:15:01.409 --> 01:15:03.629
And Dr. Riley?!

01:15:03.760 --> 01:15:06.197
We brought her in.

01:15:06.327 --> 01:15:08.895
While your sister
played nanny?!

01:15:09.026 --> 01:15:11.637
We just needed to get
proof you were an unfit mother.

01:15:11.768 --> 01:15:14.205
Get Child Services involved.

01:15:14.335 --> 01:15:18.601
But you ruined that!
You fired her!

01:15:18.731 --> 01:15:20.341
And we were left with no
choice but to escalate.

01:15:22.518 --> 01:15:25.651
- I went to prison
because of you!

01:15:25.782 --> 01:15:28.349
Where is my son?!

01:15:28.480 --> 01:15:30.351
No! No!

01:15:46.585 --> 01:15:47.368
- Oh, God!

01:16:06.649 --> 01:16:08.476
- You... will never find him!

01:16:10.827 --> 01:16:14.613
- Mark! Mark! Mark,
stop! Mark, please!

01:16:14.744 --> 01:16:16.702
Jackie!

01:16:16.833 --> 01:16:18.225
What are you doing here?

01:16:18.356 --> 01:16:20.097
- Please, okay? It doesn't
have to be like this.

01:16:20.227 --> 01:16:23.361
- Oh, God. Oh, God.
- Breathe. It's okay.

01:16:23.491 --> 01:16:25.798
- I'm so sorry.
- It's okay.

01:16:27.626 --> 01:16:29.759
No! No! No, Mark! No!
Please! Please, Mark!

01:17:16.327 --> 01:17:21.158
No. No. No!

01:17:23.464 --> 01:17:24.683
This is
my niece's house!

01:17:24.814 --> 01:17:27.686
Oh! Oh, I don't believe
this is happening to me.

01:17:27.817 --> 01:17:30.689
Okay, all right.
Let's get this ready then.

01:17:30.820 --> 01:17:33.474
Okay, five, four, three--

01:17:34.780 --> 01:17:36.216
Good evening.

01:17:36.347 --> 01:17:39.350
I'm Peggy Collingswood
of KCCO, Channel 4 News,

01:17:39.480 --> 01:17:41.395
and I'm standing outside
the front door

01:17:41.526 --> 01:17:45.138
of construction magnate
Mark Webster.

01:17:45.269 --> 01:17:47.227
The local police department
is investigating

01:17:47.358 --> 01:17:49.795
after a body was discovered
in the home.

01:17:49.926 --> 01:17:52.319
Foul play is suspected.

01:17:52.450 --> 01:17:54.670
Please be on the lookout
for fugitive Susan Webster,

01:17:54.800 --> 01:17:57.194
who was convicted
for the murder of her son.

01:18:11.164 --> 01:18:12.339
Susan, what the hell
happened to you?

01:18:12.470 --> 01:18:16.213
- This was Mark. This was Mark!

01:18:16.343 --> 01:18:19.390
He has Dylan.
Dylan is... safe.

01:18:19.520 --> 01:18:23.394
Dylan has been alive this
whole time and he's...

01:18:23.524 --> 01:18:25.613
Mark's trying to hurt me.
And he's...

01:18:25.744 --> 01:18:29.617
he's hurt my friends.
And I know...

01:18:29.748 --> 01:18:32.490
I know we aren't close,
but I need your help, Dad.

01:18:32.620 --> 01:18:35.406
Please. Please, Dad.

01:18:36.668 --> 01:18:37.974
Please.

01:18:38.104 --> 01:18:41.325
- Neil, do you actually
believe in her?

01:18:41.455 --> 01:18:43.588
Look at her.

01:18:43.719 --> 01:18:46.547
Look at that
blood! She's a convict!

01:18:46.678 --> 01:18:49.637
She's dangerous!

01:18:49.768 --> 01:18:53.859
Neil, I'm talking to you.

01:18:53.990 --> 01:18:57.254
- Neil--
- Ginny...

01:18:57.384 --> 01:18:58.559
do not talk about
my daughter that way.

01:19:03.782 --> 01:19:06.611
- Thank you. Thank you.

01:19:06.742 --> 01:19:08.221
- Hey...

01:19:10.354 --> 01:19:11.834
Okay?

01:19:11.964 --> 01:19:13.836
Mark filed a manifest
for one of our planes.

01:19:13.966 --> 01:19:15.968
It's wheels up at midnight.

01:19:16.099 --> 01:19:19.276
- Call Aunt Peggy. Tell her to
meet me there with her crew.

01:19:21.713 --> 01:19:23.671
Thank you, Dad.

01:19:23.802 --> 01:19:25.804
- Susan...

01:19:25.935 --> 01:19:28.111
there's two passengers
listed on that manifest.

01:19:28.807 --> 01:19:30.983
- Thank you. Um...

01:19:31.288 --> 01:19:33.290
Oh.

01:19:44.431 --> 01:19:47.086
911,
what is your emergency?

01:19:47.217 --> 01:19:50.263
- My name is Susan Webster.
I'm at Centennial Airbase.

01:19:50.394 --> 01:19:51.743
I'm ready to turn myself in.

01:19:51.874 --> 01:19:54.659
Ma'am, is there
an emergency?

01:19:54.790 --> 01:19:56.487
There's about to be one.

01:20:12.895 --> 01:20:15.898
Mark! Where is he?!
I know you have him!

01:20:16.028 --> 01:20:19.336
- Are you insane, Susan?!
- Where is he? You liar!

01:20:19.466 --> 01:20:20.337
You're a liar!
- You killed our son!

01:20:20.467 --> 01:20:22.556
- Stop! Let's see some ID now!

01:20:22.687 --> 01:20:25.516
- Okay. Hey, hey, no problem.
I've got my ID right here.

01:20:25.646 --> 01:20:27.387
- Please! Please! You have got
to stop him!

01:20:27.518 --> 01:20:30.086
What are you doing? I called
you guys! I called you!!

01:20:30.216 --> 01:20:33.045
- While you're at it, why don't
you run Susan Webster?

01:20:33.176 --> 01:20:35.395
- Please!
- See what you come up with.

01:20:35.526 --> 01:20:37.658
- No! No! No! Check the
plane! Check the plane!

01:20:37.789 --> 01:20:39.791
There were two passengers
listed on the manifest.

01:20:39.922 --> 01:20:41.924
Check the plane! If there's
no one in there.

01:20:42.054 --> 01:20:44.796
You should be fine letting them
check the plane! Please...

01:20:44.927 --> 01:20:47.494
- By all means...

01:20:47.625 --> 01:20:49.496
check the plane.

01:20:54.327 --> 01:20:56.852
- No! No!
- That was a thorough search.

01:20:56.982 --> 01:20:58.766
Are you sure you don't want
to check my bags, too?

01:20:58.897 --> 01:21:02.379
- Why?! Where is he?
- All right, take her away.

01:21:02.509 --> 01:21:03.380
- Anything else boys?
Or can I go?

01:21:03.510 --> 01:21:05.164
- He's lying, he's somewhere.

01:21:05.295 --> 01:21:07.775
He's trying to take him.

01:21:07.906 --> 01:21:09.125
Run his real name.

01:21:09.255 --> 01:21:11.649
It's Mark Mitchell.

01:21:11.779 --> 01:21:13.259
Please.

01:21:13.390 --> 01:21:15.740
Aunt Peggy! Aunt Peggy!
Aunt Peggy, please!

01:21:15.871 --> 01:21:18.569
Mark's trying
to take Dylan! He's here!

01:21:22.051 --> 01:21:24.531
We'd hide
in the tire well of his car.

01:21:24.662 --> 01:21:26.969
My beautiful baby boy.

01:21:27.099 --> 01:21:29.797
- The tire well. Check the tire
well. Please! Please,

01:21:29.928 --> 01:21:31.712
you have got to believe me!
Just check the tire well!

01:21:31.843 --> 01:21:33.714
Please just check the tire well!
- Peggy, what are you doing?

01:21:35.194 --> 01:21:38.545
Peggy! Peggy!!
No! No! No!

01:21:45.552 --> 01:21:47.119
Oh, my God!
Dylan!

01:21:50.601 --> 01:21:52.429
Come here. Come here,
hold my hand.

01:21:52.559 --> 01:21:54.779
Oh.

01:22:00.698 --> 01:22:02.613
Hi.

01:22:03.919 --> 01:22:07.966
Dylan...

01:22:08.097 --> 01:22:10.447
do you know who I am?

01:22:11.622 --> 01:22:12.971
- My mama.

01:22:13.102 --> 01:22:16.061
- That's right. That's right.

01:22:16.192 --> 01:22:17.236
- Oh, my.
- What were you doing

01:22:17.497 --> 01:22:19.108
in the back of the car?

01:22:19.238 --> 01:22:21.458
- Daddy said we
were playing a game

01:22:21.588 --> 01:22:24.287
of hide in the back of the car.

01:22:24.417 --> 01:22:26.811
- It's okay, baby.

01:22:26.942 --> 01:22:28.856
The game's over now.

01:22:32.904 --> 01:22:35.820
Oh, my God.

01:22:52.750 --> 01:22:53.664
- You're okay.

01:22:54.708 --> 01:22:56.493
- Susan...

01:22:58.147 --> 01:23:02.803
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.
I didn't believe you.

01:23:02.934 --> 01:23:05.110
- It's okay.
- Please forgive me.

01:23:05.241 --> 01:23:06.851
I love you so much.
- It's okay.

01:23:06.982 --> 01:23:09.114
- Thank you.

01:23:09.245 --> 01:23:11.769
Hey, little man.
How ya doin'?

01:23:11.899 --> 01:23:14.032
Oh, my God.

01:23:14.163 --> 01:23:18.515
Okay, I have do this.
You take care. Okay.

01:23:23.085 --> 01:23:25.130
Can you give me that, please?
Thank you.

01:23:25.261 --> 01:23:27.872
All right,
let's get it together.

01:23:28.003 --> 01:23:32.659
Running sound.
Five, four, three, two, one.

01:23:32.790 --> 01:23:34.270
Good evening.

01:23:34.400 --> 01:23:37.577
Tonight's top story involves
the secret life and child

01:23:37.708 --> 01:23:40.667
of construction magnate
Mark Webster.

01:23:50.677 --> 01:23:52.810
- I want to thank you all
for coming here today

01:23:52.940 --> 01:23:55.900
for the re-opening,
and appropriately renamed

01:23:56.031 --> 01:23:57.771
Women's Health Clinic,

01:23:57.902 --> 01:24:00.948
after my dear friend,
Cassie Mendoza.

01:24:01.079 --> 01:24:03.603
I wish so badly
she could be here today

01:24:03.734 --> 01:24:05.301
to meet my son, Dylan,

01:24:05.431 --> 01:24:08.478
because the truth is,
without her,

01:24:08.608 --> 01:24:10.393
I never would have found him.

01:24:12.003 --> 01:24:15.224
I'm pleased to share some of
the things that I learned her:

01:24:15.572 --> 01:24:18.879
to trust myself,

01:24:19.010 --> 01:24:21.665
to follow the truth,

01:24:21.795 --> 01:24:23.580
and to fight for our children.

01:24:26.496 --> 01:24:30.152
The privilege of being a mother
takes all that you have,

01:24:30.282 --> 01:24:33.851
the good, the bad,
and everything in between.

01:24:34.460 --> 01:24:38.769
But most of all,
it requires hope,

01:24:38.899 --> 01:24:42.642
because even if you
get lost along the way,

01:24:42.773 --> 01:24:46.429
hope will always guide you home.

01:25:40.004 --> 01:25:43.790
Subtitling: difuze
